  "description": [
    "FRIDAY MORNING OCT 6 1893 TH E LONDONDERRY SIFTER THE Londonderry Sifter So Londonderry Vermont v Mr Bohnri la Soared Apparently Carl Schnri fears the United States is on the point of annex ing Mexico and all the Central and South American republics and the outlying is lands revolutions and all One judges this to be the case from his paper on Manifest Destiny in Harpers Maga zine He begins by supposing that we annex Cuba since it is near the Florida coast very fertile and a menace to our manifest destiny Cuba being taken possession of what is to hinder annexing the Haytian islands for the same reason and that being done why should we not take in Mexico and all the rest of the Spanish Americans and incorporate them in our republic Then having already annexed all these in his mind Mr Schurz goes on to predict the dire train of evils that would follow No republio ever prospered and endured long in a tropical climate says he The reason is that in a warm cli mate people are too lazy to work stead ily being able to supply their bodily needs without it The permanency of republicanism"
  ],
